In this article, President Trump delivers remarks to members of the U.S. military stationed around the world on Christmas Day. He thanks them for their service and sacrifice, expresses his gratitude for their work in protecting and defending the country, and discusses various military operations and achievements. The President also discusses the importance of border security and the need for a wall along the U.S.-Mexico border. He addresses the government shutdown and expresses his confidence in Secretary Mnuchin and the Federal Reserve Chairman. He ends by wishing everyone a Merry Christmas and discussing the upcoming changes in the House of Representatives.